<section>
  <h2>A simple way to understand what Sigfides does</h2>
  <div class="card">
    <p>
      Most businesses don’t lose visibility because competitors publish more content or run better ads.
      They lose visibility because Google becomes unsure about their identity.
    </p>

    <p class="muted">
      “Is this the same business as this other address?”  
      “Which phone number is correct?”  
      “Is this the real location — or the old one?”  
    </p>

    <p>
      When Google is uncertain, visibility, proximity coverage and map presence quietly degrade —
      even if reviews, content and backlinks look fine.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>The problem Sigfides exists to fix</h2>
  <div class="card">
    <p>
      Over time, most businesses accumulate “identity drift” — especially those who relocate, rebrand,
      expand locations or operate in industrial estates, service areas or multi-tenant buildings.
    </p>

    <ul>
      <li>different name formats across web, GBP and directories</li>
      <li>old addresses and numbers still crawled</li>
      <li>map pins in the wrong place or wrong entrance</li>
      <li>schema and NAP details that don’t match real-world data</li>
      <li>GBP pointing to URLs that don’t reinforce local relevance</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
      To humans, everything still feels obvious.
      To Google — the entity looks unstable.
    </p>

    <p><strong>Sigfides fixes the foundation before you scale.</strong></p>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>How Sigfides works — in practical terms</h2>
  <div class="card">
    <p>We follow a staged, foundations-first approach:</p>

    <ul>
      <li>confirm your true NAP identity & coordinates</li>
      <li>create a single Canonical Identity Record</li>
      <li>align GBP → website → schema → landing pages</li>
      <li>verify crawl access, robots & sitemap integrity</li>
      <li>model your proximity confidence & trust radius</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
      When every system shows the same version of you,
      Google gains confidence — and your visibility stabilises.
    </p>

    <p class="muted">
      Learn more:
      <br>
      • <a href="/canonical-identity-signals/">Canonical Identity Signals</a><br>
      • <a href="/nap-drift-and-entity-confusion/">NAP Drift & Entity Confusion</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

